scheduler.generate
Class CourseOverlapTracker

java.lang.Object
  scheduler.generate.CourseOverlapTracker
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class CourseOverlapTracker
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Keeps track of what courses are booked for what days/times and, given a set of NoClassOverlap preferences, will ensure that class do not overlap. Written almost entirely as a convenience for me, this class's big feature is remembering when/how to remember a coure's paired lab, so as to be sure neither the lecture nor the lab for a particular course step on the toes of any other courses they are not allowed to overlap with.

Author:
Eric Liebowitz

public CourseOverlapTracker(java.util.Vector<SchedulePreference> prefs)
Builds the tracer based on a collection of SchedulePreferences. (In particular, NoClassOverlap preferences are the only one that'll be used).

Parameters:
prefs - List of SchedulePreferences (only NoClassOverlap will be considered) which will be used to setup the CourseOverlapTracker.
Method Detail

tieCoursesTogether

private void tieCoursesTogether(NoClassOverlap nco)
Creates keys in the private hashMap used to keep track of what courses are booked for what times. For a given NCO's list of coureses, each course be given the same NcoWeekAvail object, so that one's time occupation will effect the others' time availability. The MultiWeekAvail object is used to allowed courses to be constrained by multiple NCO's.

Parameters:
nco - The NCO containing the list of courses which are not allowed to overlap.

Books a given time range on a given list of days for all WeekAvail objects associated w/ a given course

Parameters:
c - The course to have time booked for
s - The start time
e - The end time
days - The days to book on
Returns:
true if the booking was made. False it is wasn't (likely b/c the entire time span wasn't free).
Throws:
NotADayException - if any of the "days" are not a valid day as defined in generate.Week.java
